-009-1331-8&amp;pmid=19247666">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">10.</div><div id="r10" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Nishie A, Asayama Y, Ishigami K, Kakihara D, Nakayama T, Ushijima Y, et al. Clinicopathological significance of the peritumoral decreased uptake area of gadolinium ethoxybenzyl diethylenetriamine pentaacetic acid in hepatocellular carcinoma. <em>J Gastroenterol Hepatol</em>. 2014;29(3):561–7.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/jgh.12423">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24219648/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Clinicopathological+significance+of+the+peritumoral+decreased+uptake+area+of+gadolinium+ethoxybenzyl+diethylenetriamine+pentaacetic+acid+in+hepatocellular+carcinoma&amp;author=A+Nishie&amp;author=Y+Asayama&amp;author=K+Ishigami&amp;author=D+Kakihara&amp;author=T+Nakayama&amp;author=Y+Ushijima&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=J+Gastroenterol+Hepatol&amp;pages=561-7&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fjgh.12423&amp;pmid=24219648">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">11.</div><div id="r11" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lee EC, Kim SH, Park H, Lee SD, Lee SA, Park SJ. Survival analysis after liver resection for hepatocellular carcinoma: A consecutive cohort of 1002 patients. <em>J Gastroenterol Hepatol</em>. 2017;32(5):1055–63.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/jgh.13632">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27797420/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Su